<font class="post">
There are two general problems with this. One, you are in a public place. If you get rowdy and start using profane language and are bothering other people, you will be asked to leave that place that you are in. So, general consensus, is act like an adult and <i>refrain</i> from using language such as that.<br /><br />Two, and more important, each time you log on to Everquest, you have to pass through the EULA (End User License Agreement). In order to play the game, you have to click on <b> I AGREE</b>. In so doing, you agree that if you DO use language that is deemed offensive, that you can and probably will be banned.<br /><br />So from one aspect, you agreed not to use that kind of language and on the other hand, we, being adults, should have the kind of restraint to not use offensive language towards others or in public channels such as /shout, /ooc and /auc<br /><br /> 
</font>
